@startuml group_chat_workflow
title Group Chat Workflow (Simplified)

actor "User A\n(Admin)" as userA
actor "User B" as userB
actor "User C" as userC
participant "Web App" as web
participant "Backend\nServer" as backend
database "Database" as db

== Creating a Group ==
userA -> web: Click "Create Group"
userA -> web: Enter name "Family Group"
web -> backend: POST /conversations\n{type: "group", name: "Family Group"}
backend -> db: Create group conversation
backend -> db: Add User A as admin
backend -> web: Group created
web -> userA: Show group page

== Adding Members ==
userA -> web: Select User B and User C
web -> backend: POST /conversations/{id}/members\n{members: [userB, userC]}
backend -> db: Add members to group
backend -> web: Members added
web -> userB: Notification: "Added to Family Group"
web -> userC: Notification: "Added to Family Group"

== Sending Group Message ==
userB -> web: Type "Hello everyone!"
web -> backend: POST /messages\n{conversation_id: group_id, content: "Hello everyone!"}
backend -> db: Save message
backend -> web: Broadcast to all members
web -> userA: Display "User B: Hello everyone!"
web -> userB: Message sent
web -> userC: Display "User B: Hello everyone!"

note right of backend
  **Group Features:**
  - Create group
  - Add/remove members
  - Admin privileges
  - Group messaging
end note

@enduml